<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2926] Document about the characteristic of HBase use HDFS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2926</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;    As our know, HDFS is design for mapreduce (streaming read/write) , and for HBase something can not fit for currently requirement. As Lipcon says, random read, sync and client fault tolerant is the most important things we should take care of. The document will make some discusses from these three points.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
