                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="12900083" author="tlipcon" created="Wed, 18 Aug 2010 22:46:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this meant to be an umbrella issue where we link to the HDFS jiras that would help us out? What&apos;s the goal of this document?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12900148" author="baggioss" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2010 01:58:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes. &lt;br/&gt;
     As we know, currently HDFS trunk can not  fit for requirement of HBase. &lt;br/&gt;
     Our goal is to get detail items where can make some improvements, such as function, stability&#65292; performance. This issue will be useful for hdfs improvement for HBase. And any helpful thing can release to this issue. &lt;br/&gt;
     Could you upload your ppt ? &lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12900592" author="hammer" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2010 06:48:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems like a reasonable thing to do. I hear a lot of concernts about HDFS from HBase folks, and it would be great to gather up the concerns in a single place so we can start tackling them one by one!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12900599" author="hammer" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2010 07:20:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ryan Rawson has pointed to the follow JIRAs that might help improve the HDFS client:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-918&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-918&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-1323&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-1323&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12900600" author="hammer" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2010 07:20:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fast local reads would probably help performance:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-347&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-347&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12900601" author="hammer" created="Fri, 20 Aug 2010 07:23:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Of course NN HA would be nice:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-1064&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-1064&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12908299" author="baggioss" created="Sat, 11 Sep 2010 10:04:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for so late reply. Currently, Chinese document is available, hope it can helpful for HBase user.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12908353" author="stack" created="Sat, 11 Sep 2010 19:08:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jinglong:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for doing this.  You doc looks excellent (smile).  Is an english translation coming?  Would you like us to put this up on our site somewhere (Would probably be better if you saved it as a pdf or html).   Does it have a date and author?  I can&apos;t tell.  If not, it should.  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12908418" author="baggioss" created="Sun, 12 Sep 2010 06:51:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
